Package: spector
Title: Computes a measure for the signal roughnes for genomic sequencing files
Version: 0.2
Authors@R: c(person("Anas Ahmad", "Rana", email = "anas.rana@oncology.ox.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre")), person("Anastasia", "Samsonova", email = "anastasia.samsonova@oncology.ox.ac.uk", role = c("aut")))
Description: The package calculates a metric estimating noise levels of genomic data, it is based on wavelet transforms. The aim is to compare the signal to noise ratio between different samples and sample preparations.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0),
  rtracklayer,
  ggplot2,
  dplyr
Import:
  ShortRead,
  wavethresh,
  readr,
  parallel
Suggests:
  knitr,
  rmarkdown
License: As per confidentiality agreement between the University of Oxford, Cancer Research Technology ltd and Genomics England ltd
LazyData: true
VignetteBuilder: knitr
biocViews: rtracklayer